   <TEXT>
   <S PAR='1' RSNT='1' SNO='1'>TRUTH LESSONS LEVEL ONE LESSON EIGHT A KEY VIEW OF THE OLD TESTAMENT 2 FROM ABRAHAM TO JOSEPH In Abraham is seen God s calling, God s promise, justification by faith, the living by faith, and the living in fellowship with God: God s calling.</S>
   <S PAR='2' RSNT='1' SNO='2'>God s promise: To make Abraham a great nation.</S>
   <S PAR='3' RSNT='1' SNO='3'>To bless Abraham.</S>
   <S PAR='4' RSNT='1' SNO='4'>To make Abraham and his seed a blessing to all the families of the earth.</S>
   <S PAR='5' RSNT='1' SNO='5'>Justification by faith.</S>
   <S PAR='6' RSNT='1' SNO='6'>Living by faith: Building an altar.</S>
   <S PAR='7' RSNT='1' SNO='7'>Pitching a tent.</S>
   <S PAR='8' RSNT='1' SNO='8'>Fighting for the brother.</S>
   <S PAR='9' RSNT='1' SNO='9'>Living in fellowship with God: Communion with God on the human level.</S>
   <S PAR='10' RSNT='1' SNO='10'>The offering of Isaac.</S>
   <S PAR='11' RSNT='1' SNO='11'>In Isaac is seen the inheriting of grace and the resting and enjoying: Inheriting grace: Born of grace.</S>
   <S PAR='12' RSNT='1' SNO='12'>Grown in grace.</S>
   <S PAR='13' RSNT='1' SNO='13'>Being the heir in grace.</S>
   <S PAR='14' RSNT='1' SNO='14'>Inheriting the promise given to his father.</S>
   <S PAR='15' RSNT='1' SNO='15'>Resting and enjoying.</S>
   <S PAR='16' RSNT='1' SNO='16'>In Jacob is seen God s selection, the transformation in life, and the maturity in life: God s selection: Before his birth.</S>
   <S PAR='17' RSNT='1' SNO='17'>Not of his own works, but of God who calls.</S>
   <S PAR='18' RSNT='1' SNO='18'>The transformation in life: Being dealt with.</S>
   <S PAR='19' RSNT='1' SNO='19'>Being met by God and receiving God s promise.</S>
   <S PAR='20' RSNT='1' SNO='20'>Being broken.</S>
   <S PAR='21' RSNT='1' SNO='21'>Being transformed.</S>
   <S PAR='22' RSNT='1' SNO='22'>The maturity in life: The heart numb, but the spirit revived.</S>
   <S PAR='23' RSNT='1' SNO='23'>No begging after arriving in Egypt.</S>
   <S PAR='24' RSNT='1' SNO='24'>Blessing people.</S>
   <S PAR='25' RSNT='1' SNO='25'>In Joseph is seen the reigning aspect of the maturity in life: Joseph s life being a part of Jacob s generation.</S>
   <S PAR='26' RSNT='1' SNO='26'>Joseph being given the authority to reign.</S>
   <S PAR='27' RSNT='1' SNO='27'>Abraham, Isaac, and Jacob, including Joseph, being three aspects of a complete experience in life.</S>
   </TEXT>
